Use the following input as an example for the test run
We first upload the ALK_mice.faa file under Input data/Option 1: Upload a FASTA file, which will store 3 protein sequences in a list
We then fetch the protein sequence under Input data/Option 3: Fetch from NCBI by Organism and Select FASTA files
- Input Organism: Homo sapiens
- Max Proteins: 100
- Iput Filter Description: NADH and Select 'Apply Filter'
- Select '3263820393 - NADH dehydrogenase subunit 6 (mitochondrion)' and Select 'Confirm Selection'
- Select '3263820392 - NADH dehydrogenase subunit 5 (mitochondrion)' and Select 'Confirm Selection'
- Select '3263820391 - NADH dehydrogenase subunit 4 (mitochondrion)' and Select 'Confirm Selection'
We should have a total of 6 protein sequences (3 from Option 1 and 3 from Option 3) stored in the same list

